{"info": {"author": "Cyril Diagne", "author_email": "diagne.cyril@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Topic :: Software Development :: Build Tools"], "description": "# ScreenPoint\n\nFinds the (x,y) coordinates of the centroid of an image (eg: a mobile phone camera image) pointing at another image (eg: a computer screen) using [OpenCV SIFT](https://docs.opencv.org/2.4/modules/nonfree/doc/feature_detection.html).\n\n![debug view](example/match_debug.png)\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install screenpoint\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nimport screenpoint\nimport cv2\n\n# Load input images.\nscreen = cv2.imread('screen.png', 0)\nview = cv2.imread('view.jpg', 0)\n\n# Project view centroid to screen space.\n# x and y are the coordinate of the `view` centroid in `screen` space.\nx, y = screenpoint.project(view, screen)\n```\n\nSee [example.py](example.py) for more information.", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "https://github.com/cyrildiagne/screenpoint/archive/v0.1.0.tar.gz", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/cyrildiagne/screenpoint", "keywords": "opencv,sift,projection", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "screenpoint", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/screenpoint/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/screenpoint/", "project_urls": {"Download": "https://github.com/cyrildiagne/screenpoint/archive/v0.1.0.tar.gz", "Homepage": "https://github.com/cyrildiagne/screenpoint"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/screenpoint/0.1.2/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Project an image centroid to another image using OpenCV", "version": "0.1.2", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>ScreenPoint</h1>\n<p>Finds the (x,y) coordinates of the centroid of an image (eg: a mobile phone camera image) pointing at another image (eg: a computer screen) using <a href=\"https://docs.opencv.org/2.4/modules/nonfree/doc/feature_detection.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">OpenCV SIFT</a>.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"debug view\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/baa52794ca89b59756bb2134ed2c6bba359885b7/6578616d706c652f6d617463685f64656275672e706e67\"></p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<pre>pip install screenpoint\n</pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">screenpoint</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">cv2</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Load input images.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">screen</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">cv2</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">imread</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'screen.png'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">view</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">cv2</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">imread</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'view.jpg'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Project view centroid to screen space.</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># x and y are the coordinate of the `view` centroid in `screen` space.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">screenpoint</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">project</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">view</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">screen</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<p>See <a href=\"example.py\" rel=\"nofollow\">example.py</a> for more information.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7155052, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "2fb46a2a1afcd3a34150c9c05bb24c0b", "sha256": "3cc22359180146cd65d7e4ec64ba4c1e42f44939431982c1ee7d7e845e463eb5"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "screenpoint-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "2fb46a2a1afcd3a34150c9c05bb24c0b", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2347, "upload_time": "2020-05-01T15:29:21", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-05-01T15:29:21.263761Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/3a/1c/fae769b6f5a8170a8114bd380fc3f8216f08e7aaf53aec9b7aa80bf0ef68/screenpoint-0.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "a88a3749c2c2a5216a48f705c228fffd", "sha256": "b7e0bb44e582fa3d2f7316e3355c37ee0add9523fd86bbf5c5911467710c76f9"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "screenpoint-0.1.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "a88a3749c2c2a5216a48f705c228fffd", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2778, "upload_time": "2020-05-01T15:42:07", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-05-01T15:42:07.008395Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/73/8b/f090b1fa5f738737efa9866a58562d49e8d5762752bb1ad201bcc23a1164/screenpoint-0.1.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "9cf39b83afce24a55c1819e7f7966c62", "sha256": "b49b63b947b71bd234a8ce175979e169522d25ceaae0e29a7ee1e5c440321837"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "screenpoint-0.1.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "9cf39b83afce24a55c1819e7f7966c62", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2783, "upload_time": "2020-05-03T06:25:14", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-05-03T06:25:14.440614Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/36/80/824d97468d04e067567dbc0dd9cad02dbb5b2ee4e3e303c73cc9f156e3c8/screenpoint-0.1.2.